NAME: Assay
DESCRIPTION: Protocol used to assay or measure an experiment sample

NAME: Bio Sample Treatment
DESCRIPTION: Protocol used to prepare Biological Sample.

NAME: Biomaterial Transformation
DESCRIPTION: Protocol used to prepare or modify a biological sample

NAME: Data Transformation
DESCRIPTION: Protocol used to analyze or reformat data

NAME: Not Specified
DESCRIPTION: Protcol Type is not specified or not received. If no Protocol Type value is received, then this is the system default value.

NAME: Study Summary
DESCRIPTION: 'Study_Summary' Study review after a study is closed.

NAME: Clinical Trials Operational Procedure Manual
DESCRIPTION: Documentation describing clinical trial-related work processes.

NAME: Institutional Review Board Independent Ethics Committee Informed Consent Document
DESCRIPTION: Records approved by the Institutional Review Board (IRB)/Independent Ethics Committee (IEC), explaining study information to assist study volunteers in understanding the expectations and requirements of trial participation.

NAME: Clinical Trial Monitoring Plan
DESCRIPTION: A proposed method to ensure the adequate monitoring of subjects during a clinical trial.

NAME: Laboratory Sample Manual
DESCRIPTION: Documentation describing work processes and procedures for the collection, handling, and shipping of a sample.
